OL,6,FThe officers were part of the Gangs
OL,7,Fand Pro-Active Team in the Central
OL,8,FSouth Command Unit and were
OL,9,Fsocialising after work when they saw
OL,10,Fthe fight unfolding.
OL,12,FTwo groups of males had been involved
OL,13,Fin a skirmish when one was struck over
OL,14,Fthe head and a dog was set on him.
OL,16,FAnother man was standing over him,
OL,17,Frepeatedly trying to slash him with a
OL,18,Flarge knife.JThe officers immediately
OL,19,Fsprang into action, rushing to
OL,20,Fseparate the attacker from the victim.
